<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="318" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Woodrow Wilson</persName> Papers</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Technical Advisers to the Commission to Negotiate
                                Peace</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Scott</hi></persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MDH1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Miller</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-30">30
                                    December, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Herewith in accordance
                            with your directions is a skeleton Draft of Peace Treaty,<note n="4" xml:id="d318fn4">
                                <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> intended as suggestive of some
                            of the questions which may arise and of the difficulties connected with
                            them. We did not understand that you wished more than an outline of
                            essentials at this time.</p>
                        <p>As an appendix to the draft, will be found a discussion of questions
                            concerning signatories to the Treaty.</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <list>
                                    <item>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_SJB1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">James Brown Scott</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_MDH1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">David Hunter Miller</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>